SIMPLE: sprinkling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sprinkling
<hw>Sprin"kling</hw> <pr>(-kl⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of one who, or that which, sprinkles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Baptism may well enough be performed by <qex>sprinkling</qex> or
effusion of water.</q> <rj><qau>Ayliffe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A small quantity falling in distinct drops or
particles; <as>as, a <ex>sprinkling</ex> of rain or snow</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Hence, a moderate number or quantity distributed
like separate drops, or as if scattered like drops.</def>
<rj><au>Craik.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sprint</ent>⟦br⟧
